metadata.name: Astraeus
metadata.description:
Astraeus, son of Crius,  
Mighty Titan of the sky,  
Bringer of the morning light,  
Illuminator of the night.

He wed Eos, goddess of dawn,  
And fathered children three,  
The winds that blow across the land,  
The stars that shine with glee.

His power was great and vast,  
His influence beyond measure,  
He controlled the weather and the seasons,  
Nature's most powerful treasure.

Astraeus, noble and true,  
His name will live forever,  
A symbol of the power of the gods,  
And the magic they can deliver.
